HOT TEA settled off the pace, raced widest into the turn, angled into the three path then back out into the lane, moved out further in upper stretch, kept on through the final furlong but needed to find more late. STRIKINGLY also raced off the pace, angled down to the inside, eased off the fence around the bend and entered the stretch three wide and could not rally. LULU LEMON DROP shook off a bump at the start and sped to the front from inside, showed the way through the turn and into the stretch, was overtaken nearing the eighth pole and weakened in the final sixteenth. EMPIRE D'ORO was unhurried when lagging behind early, saved ground through the turn and never made an impact. HAND-TIMED.
